editAddFillet(25.10)                                      editAddFillet(25.10)

Name
       editAddFillet - Adds a tear-drop fillet between a wire and bump connec-
       tion

Syntax
       editAddFillet [-help]

       Adds  a tear-drop fillet between a wire and bump connection. A teardrop
       fillet is used to reinforce the mechanical strength of  the  connection
       to  the bump. This applies to all bumps in the design. If the connected
       wire is too short to create the fillet, a marker is created to indicate
       the failure.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the command. For a detailed  description  of
              the command, use the man command:

              man editAddFillet

